---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';

---
<Base
  title="EverCheck Continuous Glucose Monitoring System | China CGM Supplier"
  description="Boost your healthcare business with our EverCheck continuous glucose monitors, featuring MARD <8%, lightweight painfree wear, IPX8 waterproof design and smart sensors."
>

<!-- NAV -->


<!-- PRODUCT HERO -->
<section class="product-hero">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="product-hero-grid">
      <div class="product-hero-content">
        <h1>EverCheck continuous glucose monitoring system</h1>
        <p>Focused exclusively on B2B partnerships, we develop reliable continuous glucose monitoring (CGM) solutions with industry-leading accuracy below 8% MARD for all types of healthcare providers worldwide. Flexible and cost-efficient, our OEM/SKD models are designed to support and scale your CGM business.</p>
        <div class="product-hero-cta">
          <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary">Contact us</a>
        </div>
        <div class="product-hero-note">
          <strong>Note:</strong> This product is designed for continuous or periodic monitoring of glucose levels in the interstitial fluid of patients with diabetes. It has been tested in adult patients (18 years and older) only. Commercialization in pediatric, pregnant, or other special populations may require additional local trials per regional regulations.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="product-hero-visual">
        <img src="/product-composite.png" alt="EverCheck continuous glucose monitoring system with mobile app showing real-time glucose data">
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- APP FEATURES -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header">
      <h2>Everything you need for smart glucose monitoring</h2>
      <p>From real-time tracking to predictive alerts, our CGMS empowers users with full visibility into their glucose health.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="app-features-list">
    <!-- 1: Real-time glucose tracking &mdash;image left, text right -->
    <div class="app-feature-row">
      <div class="app-feature-inner">
        <div class="app-feature-img">
          <img src="/cgm-app-phone-1.png" alt="EverCheck CGM app real-time glucose tracking screen">
        </div>
        <div class="app-feature-text">
          <h4>Real-time glucose tracking</h4>
          <p>Automatically updates your glucose readings every 5 minutes. See exactly how your body respond to a meal, workout, medication, or mood swing without delay. Make adjustments now, not hours later.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <!-- 2: Generate glucose curves &mdash;image right, text left -->
    <div class="app-feature-row reverse">
      <div class="app-feature-inner">
        <div class="app-feature-img">
          <img src="/cgm-app-phone-2.png" alt="EverCheck CGM app glucose curves chart screen">
        </div>
        <div class="app-feature-text">
          <h4>Generate glucose curves</h4>
          <p>Tracks your glucose 24/7 and map continuous data into clear patterns that single fingersticks can't capture. Provides long-term visibility into your glucose rhythms for better diabetes management.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <!-- 3: Predict hypo/hyperglycemic events &mdash;image left, text right -->
    <div class="app-feature-row">
      <div class="app-feature-inner">
        <div class="app-feature-img">
          <img src="/cgm-app-phone-3.png" alt="EverCheck CGM app glucose event prediction screen">
        </div>
        <div class="app-feature-text">
          <h4>Predict hypo- and hyperglycemic events</h4>
          <p>Identifies small, moment-to-moment glucose changes as they happen, including rapid rises, gentle drops, and early shifts between meals or overnight. Provides early warnings before your glucose levels become too high or too low.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <!-- 4: Customize glucose alerts &mdash;image right, text left -->
    <div class="app-feature-row reverse">
      <div class="app-feature-inner">
        <div class="app-feature-img">
          <img src="/cgm-app-phone-4.png" alt="EverCheck CGM app glucose alert customization screen">
        </div>
        <div class="app-feature-text">
          <h4>Customize glucose alerts</h4>
          <p>Create your personalized glucose limits. Receive timely notifications when your glucose levels rise above or fall below the target range, helping you stay informed and take action right away.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <!-- 5: Move freely throughout the day &mdash;image left, text right -->
    <div class="app-feature-row">
      <div class="app-feature-inner">
        <div class="app-feature-img">
          <img src="/cgm-app-phone.png" alt="EverCheck CGM app daily activity monitoring screen">
        </div>
        <div class="app-feature-text">
          <h4>Move freely throughout the day</h4>
          <p>A tiny sensor sits just beneath your skin for a pain-free, barely noticeable fit. Waterproof and designed for continuous 14-day wear, it stays comfortable through sleep, exercise, showering, and daily activities.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- KEY SPECS -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header">
      <h2>Built for accurate, continuous glucose monitoring</h2>
      <p>Industry-leading sensor accuracy with MARD below 8%, delivering trusted data for patients and clinicians alike.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="specs-grid">
      <div class="spec-card">
        <div class="spec-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="6"/><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="2"/></svg></div>
        <div class="spec-value">MARD &lt;8%</div>
        <h4>Accuracy</h4>
        <p>Delivers accurate glucose readings you can trust.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="spec-card">
        <div class="spec-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><rect x="3" y="3" width="7" height="7" rx="1"/><rect x="14" y="3" width="7" height="7" rx="1"/><rect x="3" y="14" width="7" height="7" rx="1"/><rect x="14" y="14" width="7" height="7" rx="1"/></svg></div>
        <div class="spec-value">All in <span>1</span> design</div>
        <h4>Simplicity</h4>
        <p>No assembly required before use.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="spec-card">
        <div class="spec-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M12 6v6l4 2"/></svg></div>
        <div class="spec-value">7/24 monitoring</div>
        <h4>Continuous coverage</h4>
        <p>Stay informed of your glucose levels around the clock.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="spec-card">
        <div class="spec-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M2 12h20"/><path d="M4 8h2M4 16h2M10 6h2M10 18h2M16 8h2M16 16h2M20 10h2M20 14h2"/></svg></div>
        <div class="spec-value">5.6<span>mm</span></div>
        <h4>Sensor length</h4>
        <p>Built for stable sensor placement.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="spec-card">
        <div class="spec-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><rect x="3" y="4" width="18" height="18" rx="2"/><path d="M16 2v4M8 2v4M3 10h18"/></svg></div>
        <div class="spec-value">14 <span>day use</span></div>
        <h4>Long wear time</h4>
        <p>Fewer replacements for added convenience.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="spec-card">
        <div class="spec-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M12 2.69l5.66 5.66a8 8 0 1 1-11.31 0z"/></svg></div>
        <div class="spec-value">IPX8</div>
        <h4>Waterproof</h4>
        <p>Wear confidently while showering or swimming.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="spec-card">
        <div class="spec-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M13 2L3 14h9l-1 8 10-12h-9l1-8z"/></svg></div>
        <div class="spec-value">60 <span>min warmup</span></div>
        <h4>Quick start</h4>
        <p>Ready to provide readings after a short setup time.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="spec-card">
        <div class="spec-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9"/><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="4"/><path d="M12 3v3M12 18v3M3 12h3M18 12h3"/></svg></div>
        <div class="spec-value">24.8*4.8<span>mm</span></div>
        <h4>Coin-sized</h4>
        <p>Compact size for discreet everyday wear.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="spec-card">
        <div class="spec-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M21 12a9 9 0 0 0-9-9"/><path d="M3 12a9 9 0 0 1 9-9"/><path d="M21 12c0 5-4 9-9 9"/><path d="M3 12c0 5 4 9 9 9"/><path d="M12 8v4l3 3"/></svg></div>
        <div class="spec-value">5 <span>min intervals</span></div>
        <h4>Data frequency</h4>
        <p>Receive 1000+ glucose updates throughout the day.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- SYSTEM ANATOMY -->
<section class="section section-alt">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header">
      <h2>Inside our EverCheck continuous glucose monitor system</h2>
      <p>Every CGM component works together to deliver reliable glucose monitoring</p>
    </div>
    <div class="anatomy-single-image">
      <img src="/p30-components.png" alt="Exploded view of the EverCheck continuous glucose monitor system components: applicator, transmitter, sensor, puncture needle, adhesive patch, and sterile tube, showing how each CGM part works together for reliable glucose monitoring.">
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- TECH SPECS TABLE -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header">
      <h2>Specifications of our sensor &amp; transmitter integrated kit</h2>
      <p>Complete technical parameters for our integrated sensor and transmitter, built to meet rigorous medical device standards.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="specs-table-wrap">
      <table class="specs-table">
        <tr><td>Glucose Concentration Detection Range</td><td>2-25mmol/L</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Transmitter Size (Diameter*Height)</td><td>Diameter 24.8mm*4.8mm</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Sensor Implantation Depth in Vivo</td><td>5.6mm</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Transmitter Power Supply</td><td>One lithium battery (3V) CR1025</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Service Life</td><td>14 days</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Transmitter Memory</td><td>It can store data for up to 14 days</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Operating Temperature</td><td>5-40°C</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Operating Relative Humidity</td><td>10%-90%RH</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Atmospheric Pressure</td><td>70-106KPa</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Startup Time</td><td>60min</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Wireless Transmission Distance</td><td>10m</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Waterproof Rating</td><td>IPX8</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Sterilization Method</td><td>Irradiation Sterilization</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Transmission Frequency Band</td><td>2402MHz-2480MHz</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Modulation Type</td><td>GFSK</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Effective Radiated Power (CMIIT ID)</td><td>0db</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Transmitter Memory</td><td>RAM: 96 KB  SiP Flash: 512 KB</td></tr>
      </table>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- HOW TO USE + WHY CHOOSE -->
<section class="section section-alt">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header">
      <h2>How to apply and use our EverCheck CGM?</h2>
      <p>Three simple steps to get started &mdash;apply, pair, and monitor glucose data in real time on your smartphone.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="steps-grid">
      <div class="step-card">
        <div class="step-icon">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M12 2a4 4 0 0 0-4 4c0 2.5 2 4 4 8 2-4 4-5.5 4-8a4 4 0 0 0-4-4z"/><path d="M12 14v8"/></svg>
        </div>
        <h4>Step 1: Apply</h4>
        <p>After cleaning your skin, remove the lower cover of the EverCheck CGM and place the applicator firmly and vertically on your arm. When you hear a click, the sensor has been successfully applied.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="step-card">
        <div class="step-icon">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M5 12.55a11 11 0 0 1 14.08 0M1.42 9a16 16 0 0 1 21.16 0M8.53 16.11a6 6 0 0 1 6.95 0"/><line x1="12" y1="20" x2="12.01" y2="20"/></svg>
        </div>
        <h4>Step 2: Pair &amp; warm-up</h4>
        <p>Download the EverCheck app, scan the QR code, and complete Bluetooth pairing. Wait 1 hour for the sensor warm-up to complete before readings begin.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="step-card">
        <div class="step-icon">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><rect x="2" y="3" width="20" height="14" rx="2"/><path d="M8 21h8M12 17v4"/></svg>
        </div>
        <h4>Step 3: Monitor</h4>
        <p>View real-time glucose data on your phone and receive high/low alerts. Log daily activities such as diet and exercise and gain clearer insights into your glucose patterns. Remove the transmitter after 14 days.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="section-header">
      <h2>Why choose EverCheck CGM for your healthcare business?</h2>
      <p>In-house R&amp;D, flexible partnership models, and competitive pricing &mdash;built to support your CGM business at every stage of growth.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="why-grid">
      <div class="why-card">
        <div class="why-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M3 9l9-7 9 7v11a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2z"/><path d="M9 22V12h6v10"/></svg></div>
        <h4>In-house R&amp;D and manufacturing</h4>
        <p>We own patents across key CGM technologies, including chips, sensors, and biochemical systems, backed by our 2,000 m² factory with a 10,000-class sterile cleanroom. This allows us tighter control over sensor performance, product consistency, and future optimization.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="why-card">
        <div class="why-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M12 1v22M17 5H9.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 0 0 7h5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 0 7H6"/></svg></div>
        <h4>Cost &amp; supply stability</h4>
        <p>By managing core production processes ourselves, we continuously reduce product costs and maintain stable manufacturing capacity for all clients. Scale your business confidently with our competitive pricing, reliable CGM supply and delivery timelines.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="why-card">
        <div class="why-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M17 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-4-4H5a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v2"/><circle cx="9" cy="7" r="4"/><path d="M23 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-3-3.87"/><path d="M16 3.13a4 4 0 0 1 0 7.75"/></svg></div>
        <h4>Flexible cooperation models</h4>
        <p>We support SKD for local production and CE registration, OEM rebranding, and distribution partnerships. With technical development, production, and packaging managed internally, we can adapt to different business goals and growth stages rapidly.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- FAQS -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header">
      <h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question"><span class="faq-text">What is a CGM monitor?</span><span class="faq-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>CGM stands for Continuous Glucose Monitor. Designed for diabetes management, it is a wearable medical device that continuously measures glucose levels in interstitial fluid. It provides real-time glucose trends for both patients and healthcare providers, beyond single-point measurements.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question"><span class="faq-text">Do EverCheck CGM monitors hurt?</span><span class="faq-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Most users report minimal or no pain. This is because our sensor is inserted using a fast application system, taking merely 0.2 milliseconds.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question"><span class="faq-text">How accurate are EverCheck CGM monitors?</span><span class="faq-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>CGM accuracy is typically measured using MARD (Mean Absolute Relative Difference). Our CGMS achieves a MARD of 7.94%, which positions us among leading global CGM makers in terms of accuracy. This enables us to support reliable glucose monitoring for clinical and daily use.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question"><span class="faq-text">Is EverCheck invasive or non-invasive?</span><span class="faq-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>It is minimally invasive. A thin sensor filament is inserted just under the skin and can be worn for up to 14 days. The device is coin-sized and lightweight, designed for stable daily wear with minimal sensation.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question"><span class="faq-text">How's the CE certification progress of your CGM?</span><span class="faq-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>We are currently in the process of obtaining CE certification. For SKD partners, we can also provide technical documentation and support for local regulatory applications. Please feel free to contact us to discuss your project!</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question"><span class="faq-text">What is your minimum order quantity (MOQ)?</span><span class="faq-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Since we develop and manufacture our CGM systems in-house, we're very flexible in cooperation and have no fixed MOQ. For any order size or business need, we can accommodate. Just reach out and let's see how we can support you.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question"><span class="faq-text">What does CGM measure?</span><span class="faq-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>CGM measures glucose levels in the interstitial fluid under the skin, rather than directly from blood. The main advantage is that it provides continuous, real-time glucose readings 24/7. This helps users understand how their glucose changes over time, especially after meals, exercise, and daily activities, also assists in better treatment decisions.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question"><span class="faq-text">What data can be viewed in the app?</span><span class="faq-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Users can view real-time glucose levels, historical trends, input daily activities, and receive alert notifications and glucose predictions.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question"><span class="faq-text">Can CGM replace fingerstick testing?</span><span class="faq-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>CGM provides continuous glucose trend data, but fingerstick testing may still be needed in certain situations, such as when your symptoms do not match the glucose readings. However, CGMs can greatly reduce the overall need for fingerstick testing.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question"><span class="faq-text">How long does the sensor last?</span><span class="faq-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>The sensor is designed for up to 14 days of continuous use.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question"><span class="faq-text">Can CGM be used in clinical settings?</span><span class="faq-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Yes. It is suitable for both clinical monitoring and outpatient diabetes management programs. We also offer a dedicated physician app and can adapt our system to different clinical requirements. Contact us to discuss hospital or clinical glucose monitoring needs.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question"><span class="faq-text">Where is the sensor applied?</span><span class="faq-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>The sensor is typically applied to the back of the upper arm, between the biceps and triceps. This area helps reduce the impact of muscle movement and supports stable, consistent readings during daily activities.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question"><span class="faq-text">Can I customize the product or software?</span><span class="faq-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Surely. We can customize both the product and software based on your specific requirements. Please send us a message so we can discuss your project in detail.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question"><span class="faq-text">Can I customize the CGM under my own brand?</span><span class="faq-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Yes. We support SKD, OEM and many other partnership models. Contact us and let's talk!</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question"><span class="faq-text">How often is glucose reading updated?</span><span class="faq-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Glucose data is updated every 5 minutes and transmitted to the app in real time.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question"><span class="faq-text">How reliable is the sensor performance over 14 days?</span><span class="faq-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>The sensor is designed to maintain stable performance throughout the full wear period under normal usage conditions.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question"><span class="faq-text">What alerts does the system provide?</span><span class="faq-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>The system provides configurable high and low glucose alerts, as well as trend-based predictions, to help users respond in time.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- FOOTER -->

<!-- FOOTER CTA -->
